MAX_PYRAMID_HEIGHT(arr, n)
1. Sort the array arr in non-increasing order.
2. Initialize height = 0, sum = 0, and index = 0.
3. While index < n:
     a. If arr[index] > sum, increment height by 1 and set sum to the value of arr[index].
     b. Add arr[index] to sum and increment index by 1.
4. Return height.
